Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.47,0:00:15.08,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to shine on you,\Nand always like that dazzling sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.38,0:00:18.75,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will defend you\Nfrom all the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.85,0:00:24.75,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.76,0:00:39.54,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If only our hearts could connect,\NI could get you to believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.64,0:00:46.31,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you can't\Nsee it now, don't lose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.48,0:00:54.25,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your kindness won't be in vain.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.08,0:01:01.66,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be carried aloft by the wind\Nto somewhere that isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.06,0:01:08.77,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll cross the sea and cross time,\Nand I know you'll blossom one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.93,0:01:15.41,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever the day,\NI'll be there for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.84,0:01:22.05,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hope I can watch over you\Nlike the sun for all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.05,0:01:32.02,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.74,0:01:52.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.18,0:01:55.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.05,0:01:57.85,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa isn't home?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.65,0:02:02.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like I can just leave\Nall this here and go, either...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.82,0:02:08.73,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She's out?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.96,0:02:12.20,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Looks that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.90,0:02:17.17,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's talk to the neighbours and get a\Ndescription of the people who live there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.17,0:02:18.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.65,0:02:39.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's so tranquil around here...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.56,0:02:46.56,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 17\NThe Water Mill Burns
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.03,0:03:17.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.41,0:03:33.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The prince is walking about\Non his own, buying sweets?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.09,0:03:43.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Prince Chagum.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.26,0:03:48.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shuga?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.43,0:03:57.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to see that\Nchildren's-size karru too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.31,0:04:04.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Here you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.08,0:04:13.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your Highness...\Nto find you in such a state...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.86,0:04:23.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There are too many people here.\NThis way, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.67,0:04:32.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness you are safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.47,0:04:36.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have suffered\Nhardship for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.57,0:04:40.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But those days of\Ndeprivation are now over.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.54,0:04:43.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Meeting you here is surely\Na sign from the heavens.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.11,0:04:46.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will escort you back to\Nthe palace immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.65,0:04:49.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But no, you see...I...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.29,0:04:52.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You needn't worry, Your Highness.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.89,0:04:57.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have already determined\Nwhat sort of being possesses you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.39,0:05:00.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is not something that taints you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.16,0:05:04.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is a benevolent spirit, one\Nwhich blesses our lands with water.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.70,0:05:07.27,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have informed the mikado\Nof my findings, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.40,0:05:11.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So I assure you, there is no longer\Nanyone who wishes you harm...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.18,0:05:14.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's quite a\Nself-serving speech there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.72,0:05:21.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, you must be Balsa.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.92,0:05:24.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,First you send assassins to kill him,\Nand then the instant...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.89,0:05:27.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...circumstances change, you\Nsuddenly want to bring him home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.76,0:05:29.69,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think you're\Nbeing a bit too selfish?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.69,0:05:32.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You don't understand, Balsa.\NThis man is...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.09,0:05:37.43,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,True, you have my deepest gratitude\Nfor protecting the prince thus far.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.77,0:05:40.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, he no longer\Nrequires your protection.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.50,0:05:44.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You will be exonerated of any crimes\Nand will be given a suitable reward.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.31,0:05:47.78,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can see you have\Nthe wrong idea about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.01,0:05:51.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't been protecting this boy\Nwith the aim of making money.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.18,0:05:57.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's because his mother asked me to\Nkeep him safe for the rest of his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.55,0:06:02.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The only one who can terminate\Nour agreement is the second queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.36,0:06:05.73,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I shall terminate it\Nin the second queen's stead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.63,0:06:09.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's not good enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.70,0:06:14.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After sharing life's joys and sorrows for\Nso long, your attachment is no surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.87,0:06:18.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But we can no longer afford to\Nbe swayed by such sentiments.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.01,0:06:23.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I must ask you to know your place\Nand back down without an argument.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.05,0:06:28.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but even if the\Nsecond queen were to come for him...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.18,0:06:29.85,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...I couldn't do as you ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.85,0:06:30.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.35,0:06:36.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know how much you've learned\Nabout what's possessing the boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.83,0:06:40.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...but there are compelling reasons\Nwhy I can't send him back to the palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.36,0:06:44.17,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it that you have uncovered?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.83,0:06:46.50,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Chagum.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.07,0:06:55.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your Highness!\NPrince Sagum has passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.95,0:06:58.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.65,0:07:03.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,His duties as crown prince were\Napparently too great a burden.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.65,0:07:06.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He passed away some\Ndays ago as if falling asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.79,0:07:08.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.56,0:07:12.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, Your Highness, this is no lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.90,0:07:16.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Spear-wielder, you\Nsee how things stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.20,0:07:20.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If His Highness does not return,\Nthe palace will be thrown into turmoil.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.40,0:07:24.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot humor you and your\Nso-called reasons at this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.94,0:07:27.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Leave us. A messenger\Nwill eventually be sent for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.48,0:07:28.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.15,0:07:32.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you insist on taking the prince,\Nyou'll have to kill me first.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.02,0:07:36.69,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Otherwise, I will send\Na military force after you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.25,0:07:39.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We have already\Nlocated your hideout.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.66,0:07:42.69,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Prince Chagum!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.49,0:07:47.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone is eagerly\Nawaiting your return!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.80,0:07:51.43,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I shall serve you to the best\Nof my abilities, so please!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.57,0:08:00.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum, I'll explain\Neverything on the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.21,0:08:02.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Balsa! My brother is...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.24,0:08:03.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.45,0:08:04.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shuga!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.41,0:08:06.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shuga!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.30,0:08:25.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa and the others\Nsure are taking forever...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.64,0:08:35.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I guess there's no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.79,0:08:52.93,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes my own\Nthoughtfulness amazes me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.74,0:09:06.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He put down the goods and left?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.81,0:09:07.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.11,0:09:11.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, how about you?\NDid you learn anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.18,0:09:14.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that a woman and\Nchild have been living there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.92,0:09:18.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's check out the hut.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.40,0:09:34.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They're going to Toumi village?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.51,0:09:46.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, that's... That's the chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.56,0:09:54.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,From the descriptions we've heard...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.82,0:09:58.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...there's a strong possibility that it's\Nthe spear-wielder and Prince Chagum.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.66,0:09:59.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.76,0:10:02.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What did they just say?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.78,0:10:21.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like they're out, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.95,0:10:27.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right, I'll keep watch here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.46,0:10:29.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You report back to the commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.59,0:10:32.56,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Get the word out to Taga\Nand Sune on your way back.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.76,0:10:33.93,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.77,0:10:45.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.64,0:10:47.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chief...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.71,0:10:50.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like I've blundered again!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.27,0:11:13.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What took you so long?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.87,0:11:18.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?\NDid something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.21,0:11:21.78,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We ran into someone\Nfrom the palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.75,0:11:24.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.25,0:11:27.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He wasn't a warrior, so we\Nmanaged to give him the slip.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.82,0:11:30.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We can expect pursuit soon, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.25,0:11:32.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's head straight for Toumi village.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.15,0:11:34.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But what about the supplies?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.19,0:11:38.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's only a three-day journey.\NWe'll manage.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.46,0:11:40.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I guess we'll have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.63,0:11:43.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter, Chagum?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.97,0:11:47.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The man we ran into seemed\Nto be a close acquaintance.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.47,0:11:50.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And we heard from him\Nthat Chagum's older brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.51,0:11:53.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the first prince,\Njust passed away...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.31,0:11:54.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But that means...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.91,0:11:58.38,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know, but we have more important\Nthings to worry about right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.38,0:11:59.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We have no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.92,0:12:03.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,More important things? What\Ncould possibly be more important?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.85,0:12:06.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My brother is dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.93,0:12:12.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I said that I would\Nexplain later, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.60,0:12:15.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For now, hold your tongue\Nand go on ahead with Tanda.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.83,0:12:17.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.23,0:12:21.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I left the map to\NToumi village in the hut.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.27,0:12:24.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure we'll be able to manage\Nwithout it, but I'll go get it just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.74,0:12:27.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we leave the city right now,\NI don't think anyone will see us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.78,0:12:30.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Go on ahead and\Nmeet up with Torogai.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.81,0:12:34.88,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, I think the water mill will\Nbe fine without you going back...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.02,0:12:37.85,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,it's just to be on the safe side.\NLook after Chagum.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.03,0:12:53.04,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Moribito Guardian of the Spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.91,0:13:07.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.69,0:13:18.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The errand runner's\Ndestination appears to be...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.39,0:13:21.20,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the prince's and\Nspear-wielder's lair.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.20,0:13:22.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you certain?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.23,0:13:26.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No one was home, so we did not\Nsee the prince with our own eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.14,0:13:29.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...but judging from the neighbors'\Ndescription, it is almost certainly him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.37,0:13:30.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What sort of place was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.71,0:13:33.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A water mill surrounded\Non four sides by rice fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.41,0:13:37.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Zen is keeping watch, and\NI've sent Taga and Sune on ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.11,0:13:41.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think, Commander?\NShall we launch a raid?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.35,0:13:46.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right, let's join the others\Nand confirm that it's the prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.46,0:13:54.20,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Jin. You track down Master Shuga.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.30,0:13:55.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.23,0:13:58.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Explain the situation to him\Nand have him wait here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.57,0:14:03.74,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Surely it wouldn't be too late to\Ninform him after we have confirmation...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.74,0:14:05.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Jin...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.71,0:14:09.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have a tendency to get overly\Npassionate where the prince is concerned.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.78,0:14:13.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master Shuga is\Na very prudent man.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.05,0:14:17.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Join the rest of us after\Nyou've calmed down somewhat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.39,0:14:26.53,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've written down the location here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.94,0:14:43.05,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Must dispatch pursuers...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.62,0:14:56.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hiding here won't get me anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.86,0:15:00.43,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've got to find a way to let\NBalsa know what's going on!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.17,0:15:07.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's just one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.20,0:15:11.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I run out the door and\Nbreak for the fields, maybe I can...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.95,0:15:23.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Son of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.36,0:15:35.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surrounded!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.97,0:16:12.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Jin...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.87,0:16:20.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.14,0:16:23.88,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I found Prince Chagum...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.55,0:16:25.78,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You did?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.88,0:16:28.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not long ago, I happened\Nupon him right over there...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.99,0:16:31.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Where is the prince now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.92,0:16:34.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He was led away\Nby the bodyguard...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.36,0:16:37.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe this!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.09,0:16:40.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damn, if only I had been\Nthe one who met him...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.70,0:16:43.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. The fault is mine...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.60,0:16:47.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It happened so suddenly that\NI found myself unable to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.34,0:16:49.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Where are the others?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.01,0:16:53.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yun discovered a water mill that\Nappears to be the prince's hideout.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.51,0:16:55.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone has left for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.61,0:16:59.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If the spear-wielder returns there with\Nthe prince, everything will be resolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.45,0:17:02.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if they remain at large, they...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.79,0:17:10.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I will try to find them.\NYou wait at the inn.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.76,0:17:14.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. She was\Nheaded eastwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.07,0:17:18.17,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.19,0:17:40.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now that it's come down to this...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.66,0:17:43.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've got to make sure\NBalsa and the others escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.34,0:17:59.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.81,0:18:01.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She hasn't returned?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.24,0:18:01.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.21,0:18:05.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've stationed Rai and Hyok\Non the farm roads just to be safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.25,0:18:15.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All we have to do is wait for the\Nspear-wielder to return with the prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.16,0:18:18.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Someone is inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.46,0:18:20.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.57,0:18:34.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Knowing Balsa, she'll\Nfigure out what this fire means.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.82,0:18:44.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's on fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.46,0:18:50.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?\NDid embers in the hearth start a fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.18,0:19:09.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hot! Ow! OW!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.85,0:19:15.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.79,0:19:26.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's the...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.94,0:19:40.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Were you the one\Nwho set this fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.44,0:19:45.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The people who live here,\Nwhere did they go?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.65,0:19:49.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know a thing! And even\Nif I did, I wouldn't tell you people!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.19,0:20:00.50,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You set it to warn off\Nthe spear-wielder?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.27,0:20:13.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.92,0:20:24.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Orders, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.69,0:20:28.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The spear-wielder won't show\Nherself. Not with all this commotion...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.69,0:20:31.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She might be\Nsomewhere nearby, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.66,0:20:38.57,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Should we bring him back\Nwith us and make him talk?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.40,0:20:44.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, the spear-wielder\Nis the cautious type.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.44,0:20:47.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt that this boy\Nhas been told anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.18,0:20:48.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, maybe you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.05,0:20:52.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.35,0:21:01.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm impressed that you thought\Nof setting the place on fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.02,0:21:04.93,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I respect your courage.\NBut you shouldn't risk your life like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.26,0:21:43.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Toya. I'll never\Nforget this as long as I live.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.74,0:22:27.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your Highness...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.72,0:23:13.05,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As I sat huddled and alone, holding\Nback the tears on those nights...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.05,0:23:20.20,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When it felt like I was about\Nto succumb to my doubts...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.20,0:23:25.47,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...there you were,\Nat my side before I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.47,0:23:32.81,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was none other than you\Nwho was there for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.81,0:23:47.09,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I keep wishing, "I want to be strong."\NI stumble and hurt myself again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.09,0:23:56.46,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But because I have you to believe in,\NI can get back to my feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.46,0:24:03.24,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I simply want to tell\Nmy dear one, "Thank you."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.24,0:24:08.38,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At the top of my lungs,\Nagain and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.38,0:24:16.75,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I call out to my precious loved one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.75,0:24:20.96,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is my voice reaching you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.96,0:24:29.20,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In this world that always changes,\Nhuman warmth never does.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.20,0:24:39.51,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm certain I sensed the presence\Nof the one that I hold dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.01,0:24:45.71,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next Time
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.61,0:24:46.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At the end of their path lies a Yakoo\Nvillage harkening back to bygone days.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.72,0:24:49.75,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Steam rises from earthenware pots.\NThe rice cakes are aromatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.82,0:24:52.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next time,\N"The Ancient Village."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.02,0:24:57.03,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 18\NThe Ancient Village
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.32,0:24:56.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But the storyteller\Nproclaims Chagum's death.
